## Completed Work This Session

### Project: isochron — Task #367 (ordinal date validation + CI fix)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/isochron
- `_parse_date.py`: Added ordinal day range validation (1 ≤ ordinal ≤ 365/366) before timedelta arithmetic
- `pyproject.toml`: Added isodate to `[project.optional-dependencies].dev` so `pip install -e .[dev]` installs it for CI
- `test_crossverify.py`: Changed bare `import isodate` to `pytest.importorskip("isodate")`
- `test_regressions.py`: New file with 19 regression tests for bugs #340 and #367
- All 184 tests pass, mypy --strict clean

### Project: aegis — Task #369 (OIDC/Apple nonce + SAML validation)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/aegis
- `oauth2.ts`: Added protected `_extraAuthorizationParams(req)` hook for subclass auth URL params
- `oidc.ts`: Full OIDC nonce implementation — generate, store in session, send in auth URL, validate in id_token claims; require jwks_uri for id_token signature verification
- `apple.ts`: Send nonce SHA-256 hash in authorization URL via `_extraAuthorizationParams`; fail if stored nonce exists but id_token has no nonce claim (was silently skipped)
- `saml.ts`: Fail if stored request ID exists but InResponseTo is absent (was silently skipped); require Destination attribute for HTTP POST binding (per SAML Core 3.2.2)
- Updated test SAML fixtures with Destination attributes
- All 70 tests pass, build clean

### Project: tether — Task #368 (PopenSpawn blocking + async + compat)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/tether
- `_popen.py`: Replaced blocking `stdout.read(4096)` with `select.select()` + `os.read()` — expect timeouts now functional
- `_async.py`: `send()`, `isalive()`, `terminate()`, `setwinsize()` now use `run_in_executor()`; replaced all deprecated `get_event_loop()` with `get_running_loop()`
- `_run.py`: Narrowed `except Exception: pass` to `except (ChildProcessError, OSError)` with proper exit status
- `_ssh.py`: Narrowed `except Exception` in `prompt()` to `except (Timeout, EOF)`
- `_compat.py`: EOF/TIMEOUT now map to exception classes (not sentinel types) so `except pexpect.EOF:` works
- `_expect.py`: `compile_pattern` accepts both sentinel types and exception classes
- `_types.py`: Updated Pattern union to include exception class types
- 152 tests pass, mypy --strict and pyright strict both 0 errors
- NOTE: README issues (#8, #9) deferred to documentation_writer

